Mexico Stocks: Axtel, Azteca, Homex, Penoles Shares Advance

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-06-28T21:12:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/mexico-stocks-axtel-azteca-homex-penoles-shares-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index rose for a third day, climbing 1.6 percent to
36,188.91, the biggest advance since March 23.  Telecommunications companies and homebuilders led gains on
Mexico’s benchmark index as optimism European nations will take
action to prevent a Greek default boosted demand for riskier
emerging-market assets. Two people with knowledge of the matter
told Bloomberg News that  Germany ’s biggest banks and insurers
will meet with the  Finance Ministry  in Berlin tomorrow as they
seek to reach an agreement on their contribution to a Greek aid
package.  TV Azteca SAB (AZTECACP MM), Mexico’s second-largest
broadcast television network, jumped 5.9 percent to 9.32 pesos.
Axtel SAB (AXTELCPO MM), Mexico’s second-largest land-line phone
company, gained 2.8 percent to 6.51 pesos. Desarrolladora Homex
SAB (HOMEX* MM), Mexico’s largest homebuilder, soared 3 percent
to 47.98 pesos.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s largest
silver producer, gained 1 percent to 437.29 pesos. Silver
futures for September delivery rose as much as 1.6 percent to
$34.145 an ounce on the Comex in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
